  "prompt": "How do I make Pani puri chutney in Tamil Nadu style?",
  "response": "Pani puri is a popular street food in India, and each region has its own variation of the chutney that accompanies it. Tamil Nadu style pani puri typically involves a spicy and tangy chutney. Here's a recipe for making Tamil Nadu style pani puri chutney:\n\n### Ingredients for the Pani (Spicy Water):\n- Mint leaves (pudina) - \u00bd cup\n- Coriander leaves (cilantro) - \u00bd cup\n- Green chilies - 4-5 (adjust according to spice level)\n- Tamarind - a small lemon-sized ball (soaked in water)\n- Black salt - 1 teaspoon\n- Chaat masala - 1 teaspoon\n- Roasted cumin powder - 1 teaspoon\n- Salt - as per taste\n- Cold water - 4 cups\n\n### Ingredients for the Sweet Chutney:\n- Tamarind - lemon-sized ball (soaked in water)\n- Dates - \u00bd cup (pitted)\n- Jaggery - \u00bc cup (adjust as per taste)\n- Cumin powder - 1 teaspoon\n- Red chili powder - \u00bd teaspoon\n- Dry ginger powder - \u00bd teaspoon\n- Salt - as needed\n\n### Preparation:\n\n#### For Pani (Spicy Water):\n1. **Extract Tamarind Pulp**: Soak the tamarind in water for 15-20 minutes. Extract the pulp and keep it aside.\n2. **Blend Ingredients**: In a blender, add mint leaves, coriander leaves, green chilies, and tamarind pulp. Blend to a fine paste.\n3. **Strain**: Strain the blended paste to ensure a smooth consistency.\n4. **Mix Spices**: Add black salt, chaat masala, roasted cumin powder, and salt to the mixture.\n5. **Dilute**: Add 4 cups of cold water to the mixture and stir well.\n6. **Chill**: Ideally, refrigerate the pani for 1-2 hours for the flavors to meld. Serve cold.\n\n#### For Sweet Chutney:\n1. **Cook Tamarind Pulp**: Soak tamarind and dates together in water for 30 minutes. Extract the tamarind pulp and blend dates to a fine paste.\n2. **Mix Ingredients**: Transfer tamarind pulp, dates paste, jaggery, cumin powder, red chili powder, dry ginger powder, and salt to a pan.\n3. **Cook**: Cook the mixture on a medium flame until it thickens and the jaggery melts completely.\n4. **Cool**: Let the chutney cool down. You can store this in an airtight container in the refrigerator.\n\n### Serving Suggestions:\n- **Puris**: Serve the puris crisp and hollow. Make a small hole in the puri, add a little of the spicy pani, and a dollop of the sweet chutney.\n- **Filling**: Typically, a mixture of mashed potatoes, chickpeas, and spices can be added inside the puris before adding the chutney and pani.\n\nEnjoy your Tamil Nadu style pani puri with a perfect balance of spicy and sweet chutneys!",
